										<content:encoded><![CDATA[
<p>Namaste, Welcome to Jaipur(known as Pink City), the Capital of the Rajasthan States of India.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="1600" height="1200" src="https://blog.sukantapal.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Sukanta33132_Sukanta-Pal_LR.webp" alt="" class="wp-image-453"/><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Jaipur Identity Hawa Mahal Castle inside facade. Photograph: Sukanta Pal | sukantapal.com</figcaption></figure>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>1. Hawa Mahal Castle</strong></h2>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" width="1592" height="1200" src="https://blog.sukantapal.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Sukanta33115_Sukanta-Pal_LR.webp" alt="" class="wp-image-450"/><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Sukanta Pal inside of Hawa Mahal Castle.</figcaption></figure>



<p class="has-text-align-justify">Rajput Royal Ladies in those days strictly followed the Pardah system, protecting themselves not to be seen by any stranger in public. The construction of Hawa Mahal Castle built in 1799 extension of the Royal City Palace nearby allows the royal ladies to enjoy from everyday street scenes to royal processions on the street from the small window without being seen. It has honeycomb-shaped and beautifully carved 953 windows that allow the breeze to blow through the palace, suitable to tackle summer heat in that area. This Hawa Mahal Castle(the Palace of Breeze) is now the identity of Jaipur(Top Attractions) among travellers. </p>



<p><strong>Location:</strong> Hawa Mahal Rd, Badi Choupad, J.D.A. Market, Pink City, Jaipur, Rajasthan 302002 <strong>Directions:</strong> Google <a href="https://goo.gl/maps/TcknGa3MmXivS4VbA" target="_blank" aria-label=" (opens in a new tab)" rel="noreferrer noopener" class="ek-link">Map</a>, Apple <a href="https://maps.apple.com/?address=Hawa%20Mahal,%20204,%20Tripoliya%20Bazar%20Road,%20JDA%20Market,%20Kanwar%20Nagar,%20Jaipur,%20302002,%20Rajasthan,%20India&amp;auid=1359557639707190148&amp;ll=26.923945,75.826617&amp;lsp=9902&amp;q=Hawa%20Mahal&amp;_ext=CiwKBQgEEIwBCgQIBRADCgUIBhCaAQoECAoQAAoECFIQBgoECFUQDAoECFkQARImKVLCuKI26zpAManHChaQ9FJAOU5tBFuD7TpAQXVKWCg19VJAUAQ%3D" target="_blank" aria-label=" (opens in a new tab)" rel="noreferrer noopener" class="ek-link">Map</a><br><strong>Opening Hours:</strong> Between 9:00 AM to 5:00 PM Daily (Visiting Hours)                                            <strong>Closed On:</strong> It does not close on public holidays or Sunday<br><strong>Entry Price:</strong> Indian ₹10/- Per Person + Foreigner ₹50/- Per Person                                         <strong>Website:</strong> <a href="http://hawa-mahal.com/" target="_blank" aria-label=" (opens in a new tab)" rel="noreferrer noopener" class="ek-link">hawa-mahal.com</a> </p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>2. FORTS &amp; PALACES</strong></h2>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>2.1. The City Palace</strong></h3>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" width="1600" height="1200" src="https://blog.sukantapal.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Sukanta33076_Sukanta-Pal_LR.webp" alt="" class="wp-image-448"/><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">The City Palace Main Entrance Gate. Photograph: Sukanta Pal | sukantapal.com</figcaption></figure>



<p class="has-text-align-justify">It was built by Sawai Jai Singh holds the credit of being the founder of Jaipur his residing throne. Started the construction of the palace way in the 17th century as he wanted to shift the capital of the state from Amber to Jaipur. Raja Man Singh II was the last ruler of this dynasty to hold the throne in this palace. The beautiful structure was designed by architects Vidyadhar Bhattacharya and Samuel Swinton Jacob who brought a European influence to the design. This Opulent 18th-century palace now opens the door to the public as a museum(private royal residence not for the public).</p>



<p class="has-text-align-left"><strong>Location:</strong> Gangori Bazaar, J.D.A. Market, Pink City, Jaipur, Rajasthan 302002                     <strong>Directions:</strong> Google <a aria-label=" (opens in a new tab)" href="https://goo.gl/maps/1fxD3RFMX75KAK8z8" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" class="ek-link">Map</a>, Apple <a aria-label=" (opens in a new tab)" href="https://maps.apple.com/?address=1462/1,%20Motikatia%20Bazar%20Road,%20Ramchandra%20Chaukari,%20Jaipur,%20302002,%20Rajasthan,%20India&amp;auid=12184975065915273588&amp;ll=26.925743,75.823672&amp;lsp=9902&amp;q=City%20Palace%20of%20Jaipur&amp;_ext=CisKBQgEEIwBCgQIBRADCgQIBhAQCgQIChAACgQIUhAMCgQIVRANCgQIWRABEiQpE/yPWuDVOkAxus6+jzzuUkA50GNW7hUEO0BBSjFBiTH7UkA=" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" class="ek-link">Map</a><br><strong>Opening Hours:</strong> Between 9:30 AM to 7:00 PM Daily (Visiting Hours)<br><strong>Entry Price:</strong> Indian ₹300/- Per Person + Foreigner ₹700/- Per Person                                        <strong>Ticket: </strong>Online Ticket <a aria-label=" (opens in a new tab)" href="https://thecitypalacejaipur.com/book-ticket" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" class="ek-link">Buy</a>                                                                                                                   <strong>Website:</strong> <a aria-label=" (opens in a new tab)" href="http://hawa-mahal.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" class="ek-link">royaljaipur.in</a></p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>2.2. Amer Fort &amp; Palace</strong></h3>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" width="1600" height="1200" src="https://blog.sukantapal.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Sukanta33161_Sukanta-Pal_LR.webp" alt="" class="wp-image-454"/><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Jaipur City Top View. Photograph: Sukanta Pal | sukantapal.com</figcaption></figure>



<p class="has-text-align-justify">The huge Amber Palace or Amer Fort sits atop a small hill. The fort has a number of sections, including the King’s quarters, the zenana (where the women lived), gardens, temples(including the diwan-e-aam, such mandir, and the Sheesh Mahal) etc. Amer Fort is also home to some underground tunnels that connect Amer to Jaigarh Fort.&nbsp;</p>



<p><strong>Location:</strong> Devisinghpura, Amer, Jaipur, Rajasthan 302001                                                       <strong>Directions:</strong> Google <a aria-label=" (opens in a new tab)" href="https://goo.gl/maps/1fxD3RFMX75KAK8z8" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" class="ek-link">Map</a>, Apple <a aria-label=" (opens in a new tab)" href="https://maps.apple.com/?address=Devisinghpura,%20Jaipur,%20Rajasthan%20302028,%20India&amp;auid=8808361771389828147&amp;ll=26.986278,75.850918&amp;lsp=9902&amp;q=Amber%20Fort&amp;_ext=CiwKBQgEEIwBCgQIBRADCgUIBhCTAQoECAoQAAoECFIQBgoECFUQDQoECFkQARIkKfDuiZ9f5TpAMXBXsBT671JAOeDlaxmVEztAQZKoT8/w/FJA" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" class="ek-link">Map</a><br><strong>Opening Hours:</strong> Between 8:00 AM to 5:30 PM Daily (Visiting Hours)<br><strong>Entry Price:</strong> Indian ₹100/- Per Person + Foreigner ₹500/- Per Person                                     <strong>Ticket: </strong>Online Ticket <a aria-label=" (opens in a new tab)" href="http://www.bookrajmonuments.in/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" class="ek-link">Buy</a>                                                                                                                  <strong>Website:</strong> <a aria-label=" (opens in a new tab)" href="http://hawa-mahal.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" class="ek-link">tourism.rajasthan.gov.in/amber-palace.html</a></p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>2.3. <a href="https://goo.gl/maps/D6gRHE8Er9z6we1X8" target="_blank" aria-label="Nahargarh Fort (opens in a new tab)" rel="noreferrer noopener" class="ek-link">Nahargarh Fort</a></strong></h3>



